      • write

        public final StringBuilder write(StringBuilder sb,
                                 char messagePrefix)
        Writes an encoded string representation of the event into the supplied StringBuilder.
        Parameters:
        sb - The StringBuilder that receives the encoded representation.
        messagePrefix - A prefix character used by an parser to recognize the encoded message.
        Returns:
        The StringBuilder passed as argument to allow chained StringBuilder method calls.

      • writePropertiesImpl

        protected abstract void writePropertiesImpl(EventWriter w)
        Subclasses shall provide an implementation that appends its specific properties to the encoded string representation. This method is called once and shall append all specific properties using the EventWriter.
        Parameters:
        w - The EventWriter that encodes the properties.

      • read

        public final boolean read(String message,
                          char messagePrefix)
        Reads an event from the encoded string representation. If string is not well formed, returns false, but some properties may already have been assigned.
        Parameters:
        message - The string that is supposed to contain an encoded string representation of the event.
        messagePrefix - message prefix
        Returns:
        true if an event was successfully read; false otherwise.

      • readPropertyImpl

        protected abstract boolean readPropertyImpl(EventReader r,
                                            String key)
                                     throws IOException
        Subclasses shall provide an implementation that reads its specific properties from the encoded string representation. This method is called for each encoded property.
        Parameters:
        r - The EventReader that is parsing the message. Use this parser to retrieve the property value.
        key - The property key.
        Returns:
        true if the property key was recognized, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        IOException - the EventReader failed to parse the encoded property value.
